Rule: Always consider SEO best practices when developing features or writing content for the web application. This includes:

1. Implementing server-side rendering (SSR) for better indexing.
2. Adding relevant meta tags and Open Graph tags.
3. Generating a sitemap and robots.txt.
4. Using structured data (JSON-LD) for enhanced search visibility.
5. Optimizing page speed and performance.
6. Ensuring accessible and semantic HTML.
7. Conducting keyword research and aligning content with user intent.
This rule should be applied to all development tasks and content creation to enhance the application's search engine visibility and user experience.
